  <h2 class ='list-title lead'>Theft Statistics</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>It is estimated that over 1.5 million bicycles are stolen every year. The FBI received reports of 504,000 bicycles stolen in 1995, but estimates that only <strong>one-third</strong> of all stolen bikes are reported to police.</li>
    <li>The 2000 FBI Uniform Crime Report shows the average price of a stolen bicycle is $276. With more than 313,469 bicycles reported stolen in 2000, consumers lost over $86 million.</li>
    <li>A 1994 study of bicycle theft on college campuses ... found that a four-year college student has a 53% chance of having their bike stolen.</li>
    <li>In the 92-93 school year, 11 bikes out of 100 on campuses were stolen.</li>
    <li><a target=_new href="http://www.bicyclesource.com/bike/theft/campus-theft.shtml">http://www.bicyclesource.com/bike/theft/campus-theft.shtml</a></li>
